==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[Greek]] neuter of ''phlogistos'', which meant inflammable, from ''phlogizein'', which meant to set fire on, from ''phlox''.

===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|phlogiston theory}}
'''phlogiston'''
# The [[hypothetical]] [[fiery]] [[principle]] formerly assumed to be a necessary [[constituent]] of [[combustible]] bodies and to be given up by them in [[burning]].

